  32. /*  machine-dependent definitions                              */
  33. /*  the following definitions are for the Tahoe                */
  34. /*  they might have to be changed for other machines           */

  36. /*  MAXCHAR is the largest unsigned character value            */
  37. /*  MAXSHORT is the largest value of a C short                 */
  38. /*  MINSHORT is the most negative value of a C short           */
  39. /*  MAXTABLE is the maximum table size                         */
  40. /*  BITS_PER_INT is the number of bits in a C unsigned         */
  41. /*  WORDSIZE computes the number of words needed to            */
  42. /*        store n bits                                         */
  43. /*  BIT returns the value of the n-th bit starting             */
  44. /*        from r (0-indexed)                                   */
  45. /*  SETBIT sets the n-th bit starting from r                   */

  47. ‌#define        MAXCHAR                UCHAR_MAX
  48. ‌#define        MAXSHORT        SHRT_MAX
  49. ‌#define MINSHORT        SHRT_MIN
  50. ‌#define MAXTABLE        32500

  52. ‌#define BITS_PER_INT    (8*sizeof(unsigned))
  53. ‌#define WORDSIZE(n)     (((n)+(BITS_PER_INT-1))/BITS_PER_INT)
  54. ‌#define BIT(r, n)       ((((r)[(n)/BITS_PER_INT])>>((n)%BITS_PER_INT))&1)
  55. ‌#define SETBIT(r, n)    ((r)[(n)/BITS_PER_INT]|=(1<<((n)%BITS_PER_INT)))

  150. /* MAX_ENTRY_POINT is the maximal number of entry points into the grammar. */
  151. /* Entry points are identified by a non-zero byte in the input stream,     */
  152. /* so there are at most 255 entry points.                                  */
